calibration with boostrap

kevin caye

14 fevrier 2017

library(tidyverse)
library(Article3Package)

On gaussian dataset

cs <- c(0.6, 0.3, 0.0)
K <- 3
s <- NormalSampler2(n = 100,
                    L = 1000,
                    K = 3,
                    prop.outlier = 0.2,
                    cs = cs)
expPCA <- PCAExperiment(s)
expPCA <- runExperiment(expPCA)
plot(expPCA) + 
      scale_x_continuous(limits = c(1,60))

bootstrapCalibration(s = s, 
            method.K = K , 
            lambda.lfmmridge = 1e-5,
            exp.rep = 3)
Hypothesis testing comparison

On logistic dataset

c <- 0.6
K <- 6
s <- LogisticSampler(n = 100,
                    L = 1000,
                    K = K,
                    prop.outlier = 0.2,
                    c = c)
expPCA <- PCAExperiment(s)
expPCA <- runExperiment(expPCA)
plot(expPCA) + 
      scale_x_continuous(limits = c(1,60))

bootstrapCalibration(s = s, 
            method.K = K, 
            lambda.lfmmridge = 1e-5,
            exp.rep = 3)
Hypothesis testing comparison
